The paper proposes an end-to-end system that uses vector representations to find similar questions for unsolved medical questions on crowdsourced Q&A websites. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CY). However, since the paper focuses on text-based question answering, we can rule out cs.CV and cs.GR, which are more related to image and graphics processing.
